  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:"Born in Pisidia, died in c. AD 631/634. Diákonos, 
    skeuophýlax and referendários at the church of St. Sophia in Constantinople, one of the greatest 
    Byzantine poets. Highly revered and often imitated, G. treats the Persian campaign of Emperor
    Heraclius (Expeditio Persica, Bellum Avaricum, Heraclias, etc.) in his epic-encomiastic ....
    poems, and deals in part with philosophical, in part with purely dogmatic topics in his theological 
    works (Hexaemeron, a didactic poem that was translated also into Armenian and Slavic,..." 
    Vassis, Ioannis (Athens). "Georgius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2010. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 20 December 2010 .</mads:note>
